  "doc_id": "12530",
  "text": "Because of the abundance of S100A8/A9 in myeloid cells compared with nonmyeloid cells, myeloid-derived S100A8/A9 are believed to mediate the effects of whole-body S100A9 deficiency. However, S100A8 and S100A9 can be induced by inflammatory stimuli in nonhematopoietic cells, eg, endothelial cells. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Therefore, the goal of this study was to investigate whether myeloid-derived S100A8/A9 contribute to atherosclerosis. Insulin resistance was analyzed as a secondary end point.",
